         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden ¶ 20/5/64. ¶ Dear Mr Davenport ¶  ¶ I must not be remiss in expressing my gratification to hear of Mrs Davenports return and to congratulate your Lady to the success that has att...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">64.05.20a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Samuel Davenport</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">PRG 40/20, Mortlock Library, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">20/5/64.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mr Davenport</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I must not be remiss in expressing my gratification to hear of Mrs Davenports return and to congratulate your Lady to the success that has attended her effort to bring the Ailantus Silkworm to Australia, a fact which for ever will identify her name with the new industry thereby initiated in this country.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You speak of the mulberry silkworm, but this is largely established in Australia at least in this colony. The spurious Quinoa has also well grown here. I take the liberty of using the expression spurious because the true Quinoa is Chenopodium Quinoa, whilst the plant which we raised is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Amarantus<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>paniculatus. The grain however of both is nutritious.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Accept my best thank for the seeds of Olives, all fine varieties.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With expressions of kindest regard for you &amp; Mrs Davenport</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain, dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours cordially</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Amarantus paniculatus</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Chenopodium Quinoa</p>
